\begin{frame}[t]{The heat-transfer cliff (conceptual boiling curve)}
\begin{columns}[T,onlytextwidth]
\column{0.52\textwidth}
\begin{block}{Why CHF matters}
\begin{itemize}
  \item Before CHF: nucleate boiling is a superpower (high heat-transfer coefficient).
  \item At CHF: the wall can\'t stay reliably wetted.
  \item After CHF: vapor insulation dominates \textrightarrow{} wall temperature rises fast.
\end{itemize}
\end{block}

